    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix usage() function behavior in multi.c tracer\n\n### Summary\nThe usage() function in the multi tracer was not behaving as expected when called. This change improves the function's behavior by sending output to stderr and ensuring proper formatting.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/multi.c`: Modified usage() function to use fprintf(stderr, ...) instead of printf() and added trailing newline for proper formatting\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the multi tracer with -h or --help flag, or when incorrect parameters are passed, the usage message was not displaying correctly in some terminal environments. The issue was particularly noticeable when the output was redirected or piped to other commands.\n\nUsers reported that the help message would sometimes appear garbled or would not display at all in certain environments. With this fix, the usage message now properly goes to stderr and includes proper line termination.\n\n"
}